  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of national and international regulations:\n\n1. Key International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group protocols\n\n2. National Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- Similar comprehensive legislation in most countries\n\n3. Core Legal Requirements:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Criminal Penalties:\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n5. Regulatory Oversight:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banking authorities\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Specialized investigative units\n\n6. Key Compliance Mechanisms:\n- Risk-based assessment approaches\n- Enhanced due diligence\n- Ongoing transaction screening\n- Regular internal audits\n\n7. International Cooperation:\n- Information sharing agreements\n- Cross-border investigation protocols\n- Extradition arrangements\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
